When the application server starts the default behavior for Confluence is to unload and upgrade every plugin even if components have not been upgraded. According to Atlassian support this is default behavior and the way that Confluence loads plugins into the cache. The problem is that load times for the J2EE container are very long while the caching occurs. If there could be a way to set plugin caching to be dynamic or spawn a separate thread to cache plugins so that the rest of the application server could start up faster, that would be very helpful.

