Currently when I use the jiraisues macro in confluence, there is a link at the top of the portlet which returns the xml issue list. Unfortunately users tend to click on this thinking they'll go to the Jira issue navigator, and are deeply disappointed and perplexed at the results.

The same is true when I use a count=true jiraissue macro to show the number of issues; this is linked, users expect it to go to a nice familiar html list of issues, but are instead assaulted with "yucky" xml.

I can understand wanting the xml, as it's handy for those of us into feed readers, but for most of my users it's not useful. So if we could have a parameter that lets us specify a link to the issue navigator, it would be very handy.

When changing the title of a page, links are not updated. Links which are listed as incoming links of this page are updated correctly.
This occurs when the links are in the bodies of some macros. 

Eg
